<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>draught of ro owns sunstrike even without focus items. I don't even scribe ss anymore. GSS while ooo awww it sucks now compared to the easier to attain counterpart Strike of Solusek. EER sucks now compared to the easier to attain Agnarr's Thunder.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
Actually with the instacast refresh change, DoR has a lower potential dps than SS (even when both are focused) when resists are not a factor (SS 232.3 dps vs DoR 229.7 dps).  If SS was focused and DoR was not, DoR would be 4.13 dmg/mana and SS would be 5.17 dmg/mana.  But that is not really why I am upset with the availability of those 2 Luclin spells.<br>
<br>
In order to even scribe DoR you need to be 62, AT 63, SoS 65.  So you have to abandon a great deal of pre-PoP content as well as get the PoP spells.  It now appears that VI is not done providing content geared to the sub-PoP levels.  There was a post in the General forum about PoP.  The gist of the thread said upper PoP was not for everyone; which in turn can mean that 61+ is not for everyone.  There are many reasons to stay in the low 60s, especially for those in smaller or diverse leveled guilds.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>why are you guys still whining?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
We are not 'whining'.  This is still a valid issue for people in these levels.  VI is still tuning sub-60 content (i.e. Beastlord rare Luclin spells now on a vendor).  <br>
