HEALING is not your prime function by any means, never has been, never will be.  Should it be so rare?  No, i don't think so, but it is a very bad comparison to make with GSS since NUKING is a wizard's prime function.  The rarity of GSS would not be such a huge sticking point if 1. SS and EER were not also ridiculously rare, leaving only ice spear, a 1200 point, often resisted nuke for the average lvl 60 wizard   and  2. if FoT which is on a vendor was not clearly balanced off GSS but instead had been balanced off our common nuke, ice spear.<br>
<br>
As Raz said, i think it was an honest oversight on SOE's part.  They were so focused on fixing the damage the mod rod nerf did to mages that they seem to have forgotten that wizards are specialized nukers and that GSS is extremely rare.  The only way to fix that at this point is to either deal with our spell rarity at that level range, or add a vendor nuke for wizards at 61 which is balanced with FoT in mind.  Unfortunately it is clear to me that they will never deal with this inequity. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gwideonthegnome>GwideonTheGnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/4/03 11:30:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=789.topic&index=40>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Most mages...</span><hr size=1> Gnomish Greetings!<br>
